		"title": "CVE-2024-27037 on Ubuntu 18.04 FIPS Certified (bionic) - medium",
		"description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: clk:zynq: Prevent null pointer dereference caused by kmalloc failure Thekmalloc() in zynq_clk_setup() will return null if the physical memory hasrun out. As a result, if we use snprintf() to write data to the nulladdress, the null pointer dereference bug will happen. This patch uses astack variable to replace the kmalloc().",
